  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean package)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package honestly documents one explicitly low-confidence factor (model inputs: blood viscosity parameters carry wide Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds) while all other factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. The low-confidence gap in model inputs is fully characterised with quantified uncertainty bounds, sensitivity analysis, and a documented acceptance rationale explaining why the residual uncertainty does not invalidate the hemolysis predictions at the operating envelope assessed. Decision: Accepted with documented epistemic gap in model inputs.",
