      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5",
      "rationale": "EXPLICITLY FLAGGED LOW-CONFIDENCE INPUT — HONESTLY DOCUMENTED: Blood viscosity parameters (Carreau-Yasuda model constants) carry wide epistemic uncertainty due to donor-to-donor variability in the source literature (CV 18–24% on zero-shear viscosity; CV 12% on power-law index). This is the primary driver of the 90% Monte Carlo prediction interval width (±31% on peak MIH). Confidence score assigned: 0.71 (moderate-high, not high). Full sensitivity analysis confirms that even at the 95th-percentile viscosity parameter combination, predicted MIH remains 14% below the clinical acceptance threshold. The uncertainty is therefore bounded, quantified, and does not invalidate the acceptance decision. All other model inputs (geometry, rotational speed, inlet flow rate, hematocrit) carry confidence scores ≥0.92. The low-confidence viscosity gap is documented as an epistemic limitation requiring re-evaluation if the device operating envelope is extended beyond the 5 assessed conditions. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3 because the quantified uncertainty bound is demonstrably conservative relative to the clinical threshold margin."
