  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-hemolysis-cou2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed. All 13 factors achieve levels meeting or exceeding their required levels for MRL 5 / Class III device context. One factor — model inputs (blood viscosity parameters) — carries an explicitly documented low-confidence score (0.71) due to donor-to-donor variability in Carreau-Yasuda constants. This uncertainty has been fully quantified via Monte Carlo analysis (n=5000) and a comprehensive sensitivity study. The key finding is that even under the 95th-percentile adverse viscosity parameter combination, predicted peak MIH remains 14% below the absolute clinical acceptance threshold. The uncertainty is therefore bounded, conservative, and does not undermine the acceptance decision for the 5 assessed operating conditions. The epistemic gap is formally documented as a scope limitation: any extension of the operating envelope beyond the 5 assessed flow-speed combinations would require re-evaluation of this factor. The provenance chain is complete: all validation results link to primary experimental datasets, Monte Carlo UQ records, and generating activities. The decision to Accept is grounded in the structured evidence, the quantified uncertainty margin relative to the clinical threshold, and the explicit documentation of the one low-confidence input parameter. No weakeners are present in this package.",
